<p><font face="Verdana" size="18">Delete Tables</font></p>
<p></p>
<p>Deleting Tables in SQL is very easy. It uses the SQL command:</p>
<p></p>
<p>DROP TABLE &lt;table_name&gt;</p>
<p></p>
<p>Here's the code to delete the <b>users</b> table:</p>
<p></p>
<p><font face="Courier New" size="14">put &quot;DROP TABLE users&quot; into tSQL</font></p>
<p><font face="Courier New" size="12">put revExecuteSQL(&lt;connectionID&gt;,tSQL) into tTmp</font></p>
<p><font face="Courier New" size="12">-- tResult contains the number of tables dropped.</font></p>
<p></p>
<p>You can press the button <b>Delete users Table</b> to test it. Press it again to confirm the table has been deleted.</p>
<p>Press the <b>Default Data</b> button to 'reset' the database with the default tables and values.</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>